":"For example, if a parent feature models a navigation stack of child features using the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackState","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackAction","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" types, then it can perform its core logic ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"and"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" the logic","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of each child feature using the ","type":"text"},{"code":"forEach","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" operator:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@Reducer","struct ParentFeature {","  struct State {","    var path = StackState<Path.State>()","    \/\/ ...","  }","  enum Action {","    case path(StackActionOf<Path>)","    \/\/ ...","  }","  var body: some ReducerOf<Self> {","    Reduce { state, action in","      \/\/ Core parent logic","    }","    .forEach(\\.path, action: \\.path) {","      Path()","    }","  }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"forEach","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" operator does a number of things to make integrating parent and child features","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ergonomic and enforce correctness:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It forces a specific order of operations for the child and parent features:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackAction\/element(id:action:)"},{"type":"text","text":" action is sent it runs the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"child first, and then the parent. If the order was reversed, then it would be possible"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the parent feature to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" out the child state, in which case the child feature"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"would not be able to react to that action. That can cause subtle bugs."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackAction\/popFrom(id:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" action is sent it runs the parent feature","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"before the child state is popped off the stack. This gives the parent feature an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"opportunity to inspect the child state one last time before the state is removed.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackAction\/push(id:state:)"},{"text":" action is sent it runs the parent feature","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"after the child state is appended to the stack. This gives the parent feature an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"opportunity to make extra mutations to the state after it has been added.","type":"text"}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It automatically cancels all child effects when it detects the child’s state is removed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from the stack","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It gives the child feature access to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/DismissEffect"},{"text":" dependency, which allows the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"child feature to dismiss itself without communicating with the parent.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/BindingReducer\/forEach(_:action:destination:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-58r5h","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/BindingReducer","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/BindingReducer\/Reducer-Implementations"],["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SwiftUIIntegration","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/BindingReducer","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/BindingReducer\/Reducer-Implementations"]]},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/bindingreducer\/foreach(_:action:destination:fileid:filepath:line:column:)-58r5h"]}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:22ComposableArchitecture7ReducerPAAE7forEach_6action11destination6fileID0H4Path4line6columnQrs011WritableKeyJ0Cy5StateQzAA05StackO0Vyqd__GG_s0nJ0Cy13CasePathsCore0Q0Vy6ActionQzGAWyAA0pT0Oyqd__qd_0_GGGqd_1_yXEs12StaticStringVA5_S2utAMQyd_1_Rsd__AXQyd_1_Rsd_0_AaBRd_1_r1_lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:22ComposableArchitecture14BindingReducerV","extendedModule":"ComposableArchitecture","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"